Raw OVS and ping output for the KubeVirt + Multus + OVS-CNI secondary-network lab.
================================================================================

Why this file is named .tt and not .json
-----------------------------------------
The assignment's `Readme.md` asks for `verification_flows.json` produced by
`ovs-ofctl dump-flows <bridge> --format=json`. The OVS version installed on
this host (ovs_version "3.5.0", per `ovs-vsctl show`) does NOT support
`--format=json` on the dump-flows subcommand:

  $ ovs-ofctl dump-flows br-ovs --format=json
  ovs-ofctl: unrecognized option '--format=json'

  $ ovs-ofctl dump-flows br-ovs -F xml
  ovs-ofctl: xml: unknown flow protocol

`verification_flows.json` was therefore hand-written from the raw text below
and embeds the captured flow + port state + ping result as structured fields
under the `structured_fields` / `_port_state` / `_vm_evidence` keys. This
file is the ground truth: plain text from the host, untouched.

Captured at: ~ 2026-07-06, after the VM was in `Running`/`Ready: True`
phase on the live cluster, and after `ip addr add 192.168.200.2/30 dev eth0`
was run inside the CirrOS console (the cloud-init runcmd in our manifest
did not run on this image; see notes at bottom of this file).


1. OVS flow dump on br-ovs
-------------------------
$ sudo ovs-ofctl dump-flows br-ovs
 cookie=0x0, duration=188283.697s, table=0, n_packets=378, n_bytes=35828, priority=0 actions=NORMAL

(One default flow. n_packets / n_bytes increment as VM traffic flows
through br-ovs; initial measurement on the live cluster was taken after
the host-to-VM ping captured in section 4.)


